<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>

<head>
  <title>Oxford-Style Debate Research</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles.css">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
</head>

<body>
  <div class="container" style="width: 800px;">
    <div class="study-card">
      <h1>Oxford-Style Debate Research</h1>
      
      <div class="welcome-content">
        <p>Welcome to the Oxford-Style Debate Platform research study. This platform allows you to engage in structured debates with AI language models.</p>
        
        <div class="info-box">
          <h3>About This Study</h3>
          <p>This research examines how large language models (LLMs) perform in structured Oxford-style debates when compared with human debaters. Your participation will help establish a high-quality human benchmark for evaluating AI-generated argumentation.</p>
          
          <p>You'll participate in a series of short debates against one or more LLMs. Each debate contains three short turns per side, with a 100-150 word limit per turn.</p>
        </div>
        
        <h3>How to Participate</h3>
        <p>To begin, please review the study information and consent form.</p>
        
        <div class="button-container">
          <a href="/consent" class="button">Begin Participation</a>
          <a href="/dev" class="button button-secondary">Development Mode</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</body>

</html>